title: 5 Seconds of Summer to perform at Palace in July
text:
Tickets for the group’s show go on sale Oct. 23; pre-sales begin Tuesday Luke Hemmings of 5 Seconds of Summer performs at the Nikon at Jones Beach Theater on Tuesday, Sept. 1, 2015, in Wantagh, N.Y. (Photo: Greg Allen / Invision/AP) 
Australian heartthrobs 5 Seconds of Summer are giving fans plenty of notice for their upcoming tour.
Fans of the foursome will want to clear July 27 on their calendars — that is the date the group will play the Palace of Auburn Hills, reps for 5SOS announced Friday.
Tickets for the show go on sale Oct. 23, and will be preceded by a pre-sale for members of Citi’s Private Pass Program beginning at 10 a.m. Tuesday. Fans who pre-order the band’s new album “Sounds Good Feels Good” (in stores Oct. 23) through the band’s online webstore will also get an early crack at tickets.
The July concert will mark the group’s second consecutive year headlining the Auburn Hills arena; the group also performed there in August.
